T1  - Testing the autoregressive parameter with the t statistic
AU  - Nankervis, J.C.
AU  - Savin, N.E.
JO  - Journal of Econometrics
VL  - 27
IS  - 2
SP  - 143
EP  - 161
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/02/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(85)90084-3
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407685900843
AB  - This paper considers a Gaussian first-order autoregressive process with unknown intercept where the initial value of the variable is a known constant. Monte Carlo simulations are used to investigate the sampling distribution of the t statistic for the autoregressive parameter when its value is in the neighborhood of unity. A small sigma asymptotic result is exploited in the construction of exact non-similar tests. The powers of non-similar tests of the random walk and other hypotheses are estimated for sample sizes typical in economic applications.
