EP  - 196
PY  - 1985
DA  - 1985/02/01/
SN  - 0304-4076
DO  - https://doi.org/10.1016/0304-4076(85)90086-7
UR  - https://www.sciencedirect.com/science/article/pii/0304407685900867
AB  - It is well known that generalised least-squares estimators of a set of regression equations coincide with ordinary least-squares estimators when the explanatory variables are the same in all equations and there are equal numbers of observations. This paper is concerned with the case of unequal numbers of observations and it is shown that the above result no longer holds. Appropriate estimators are derived and their small-sample properties are investigated analytically. The results are of practical importance because the data patterns discussed can easily arise in econometric studies.
